            <p>
            Despite the ravages of fire, Balanga has many large structures. One of the oldest provincial government building in the archipelago is found in this town. It was erected in 1729. Balanga was inaugurated as a city on December 30, 2000 by virtue of Republic Act 8984. For the last ten years, there has been a rapid economic growth in its urban areas. Commercial establishments, including financing institutions have proliferated in the City. 
